article.headline: Kansas St. 83, Idaho St. 57
article.story: MANHATTAN, Kan. -- Jamar Samuels scored 15 points to lead Kansas State to a 83-57 win over Idaho State on Saturday. Jacob Pullen added 12 for the Wildcats (10-3). Matt Stucki and Phyllip Taylor led the Bengals (4-11) with 13 and 10 points respectively. The Bengals struck first on a layup by Stucki, but back-to-back 3-pointers by Pullen gave the Wildcats the lead for good. After falling behind 25-13, Idaho State narrowed the gap to eight, but scored just five points in the final 9:30. Kansas State ended the half on an 8-1 run to take a 40-22 lead into intermission. Stucki opened the second half with a pair of free throws, but Kansas State responded with a 9-1 run to push its lead to 49-25. The Bengals got within 18 on a 9-3 run midway through the half, but a pair of free throws by Pullen extinguished the comeback attempt.
